OL,3,CWoman begged armed hotel intruder
OL,4,C'don't hurt me, I have children'
OL,6,FShe opened the door and Prior pushed
OL,7,Fhis way past her into the room,
OL,8,Fholding a knife in his right hand.
OL,10,F"She shouted for help," Mr Masson
OL,11,Fsaid.J"The defendant told her to stop
OL,12,Fshouting and that he was not going to
OL,13,Fhurt her."
OL,15,FPrior shut the door and the woman
OL,16,Fbacked away.
OL,18,FShe told him: "Please don't hurt me. I
OL,19,Fhave got children."JThe prosecution
OL,20,Fsaid Prior told the woman that he
OL,21,Fneeded somewhere to hide.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G3/6
