OL,3,CWoman begged armed hotel intruder
OL,4,C'don't hurt me, I have children'
OL,6,F"She told him that he could stay and
OL,7,Fthat she would leave but he told her
OL,8,Fto stay in the room," said Mr Masson.
OL,10,F"She was absolutely terrified. She
OL,11,Fthought that she was about to be
OL,12,Fmurdered."
OL,14,FHe left the room after about three
OL,15,Fminutes.JThe woman said that she had
OL,16,Fbeen left traumatised after what she
OL,17,Fdescribed as the most terrifying
OL,18,Fexperience of her life.
OL,20,FShe was receiving therapy and her work
OL,21,Fhad been affected, the court heard.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G4/6
